message.content:
There are several suspicious processes with open sockets in the provided data:

1. Process ID 888 (firefox.exe) has a TCP connection open to 127.0.0.1 on port 1168.
2. Process ID 1244 (svchost.exe) has TCP connections open to local addresses on ports 1189 and 2869.
3. Process ID 4 (System) has a TCP connection open to 192.168.0.176 on port 139.
4. Process ID 880 (svchost.exe) has a TCP connection open to 0.0.0.0 on port 1185.

These connections could be indicative of suspicious network activity related to the suspected phishing attack targeting alg.exe. Further analysis and investigation into these processes and connections are recommended to determine if they are indeed part of the security breach.
